snippet: An election year challenge sure to stump even the most astute Republicans in this state: Name one issue on which the party's two main contenders for a six-year Senate term agree.   Give up? So do the candidates themselves....
lead_paragraph: An election year challenge sure to stump even the most astute Republicans in this state: Name one issue on which the party's two main contenders for a six-year Senate term agree. Give up? So do the candidates themselves.

headline.main: THE 1992 CAMPAIGN: Senate Race Primaries for Cranston's Seat Expose Rifts in California Parties' Ideologies; Republicans View Contest for Heart of Their Party
